org.treetank.settings
Enum ERevisioning

All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<ERevisioning>
public enum ERevisioning
extends Enum<ERevisioning>

Enum for providing different revision algorithms. Each kind must implement one method to reconstruct NodePages for Modification and for Reading.

Author:
Sebastian Graf, University of Konstanz

Enum Constant Detail

FULLDUMP

public static final ERevisioning FULLDUMP
FullDump, Just dumping the complete older revision.

DIFFERENTIAL

public static final ERevisioning DIFFERENTIAL
Differential. Only the diffs are stored related to the last milestone revision

INCREMENTAL

public static final ERevisioning INCREMENTAL
Incremental Revisioning. Each Revision can be reconstructed with the help of a the last full-dump plus the incremental steps between.

combinePages

public abstract NodePage combinePages(NodePage[] pages,
                                      int revToRestore)
Method to reconstruct a complete NodePage with the help of party filled pages plus a revision-delta which determines the necessary steps back.

Parameters:
pages - the base of the complete Nodepage
revToRestore - the revision needed to build up the complete milestone.
Returns:
the complete NodePage

combinePagesForModification

public abstract NodePageContainer combinePagesForModification(NodePage[] pages,
                                                              int mileStoneRevision)
Method to reconstruct a complete NodePage for reading as well as a NodePage for serializing with the Nodes to write already on there.

Parameters:
pages - the base of the complete Nodepage
mileStoneRevision - the revision needed to build up the complete milestone.
Returns:
a NodePageContainer holding a complete NodePage for reading a one for writing
